		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in httpd. A HTTP response splitting in multiple httpd modules may allow an attacker that can inject malicious response headers into backend applications to cause an HTTP desynchronization attack. \n            STATEMENT: This flaw is only exploitable by a malicious backend in a reverse proxy configuration or an attack against a backend application which inserts headers.",
